void container::LinkedList_test::generateDataAndPopulateList ( Entity **&  data,
LinkedList *&  a,
const int  listSize,
bool  print = false 
) [inline, protected]

Creates a new test data set.

A new data array is created and a new LinkedList. Both are populated with the same list of Entities. It is the responsibility of the caller to release all objects created: the array of Entity pointers, the LinkedList, and all the Entity objects.

Postcondition:
A new array of Entity pointers is created.

A new Linked List is created.

SIZE number if Entity objects are created.

The data array and the LinkedList will both be populated with pointers to the newly created Entity objects.

The order will be the same in both the data array and the LinkedList.

00139       a = new LinkedList();
